        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>André Michaux was a French botanist and traveler.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <odd id="ref14">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>The Collection consists of nine small journals Andre Michaux kept as he traveled throughout North America. His travels took him to places as far and wide as the Caribbean, Kentucky, and Hudson’s Bay. The journal has been printed in APS’s Proceedings 26 (1889):1. The Kentucky travels can be found in Reuben G. Thwaites’ Early Western Travels, 1748-1846.</p>
        </odd>
